com.asoroka.sidora.tabularmetadata.heuristics.enumerations

Interface EnumeratedValuesHeuristic<SelfType extends EnumeratedValuesHeuristic<SelfType>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, Heuristic<SelfType>, javax.inject.Provider<SelfType>, SelfTypeInstanceGenerator<SelfType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InMemoryEnumeratedValuesHeuristic

    public interface EnumeratedValuesHeuristic<SelfType extends EnumeratedValuesHeuristic<SelfType>>
extends Heuristic<SelfType>
    A heuristic to enumerate lexes as recognized by type.
    Determines a Map from DataType to a Set of lexes chosen from the lexes supplied to this heuristic. A lex will be included in the set for a given datatype if and only if it was found to be parseable into that type. For example, all lexes will be included in the set for DataType.String, since any lex can be parsed as a String, but if the lexes presented are {"1","Foo","34,56"}, then the set for DataType.Integer will include only "1".

    ajs6f
